{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"ImageCapture.takePhoto()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/takePhoto","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture\"><code>ImageCapture</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/ImageCapture\"><code>ImageCapture() constructor</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/track\"><code>track</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/getPhotoCapabilities\"><code>getPhotoCapabilities()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/getPhotoSettings\"><code>getPhotoSettings()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/grabFrame\"><code>grabFrame()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><em><code>takePhoto()</code></em></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>takePhoto()</code></strong> method of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture\"><code>ImageCapture</code></a> interface takes a single exposure using the video capture\n  device sourcing a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaStreamTrack\"><code>MediaStreamTrack</code></a> and returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a>\n  that resolves with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a> containing the data.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">takePhoto()\ntakePhoto(photoSettings)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"photosettings\"><code>photoSettings</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object that sets options for the photo to be taken. The available options are:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"filllightmode\"><code>fillLightMode</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          The flash setting of the capture device, one of\n          <code>\"auto\"</code>, <code>\"off\"</code>, or <code>\"flash\"</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"imageheight\"><code>imageHeight</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          The desired image height as an integer. The user agent\n          selects the closest height value to this setting if it only supports discrete\n          heights.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"imagewidth\"><code>imageWidth</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          The desired image width as an integer. The user agent\n          selects the closest width value to this setting if it only supports discrete\n          widths.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"redeyereduction\"><code>redEyeReduction</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean indicating whether the red-eye reduction\n          should be used if it is available.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  This example is extracted from this <a href=\"https://simpl.info/imagecapture/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Simple Image Capture demo</a>. It shows how to use the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> returned by\n  <code>takePhoto()</code> to copy the returned <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Blob\"><code>Blob</code></a> to an\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/img\"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a> element. For simplicity it does not show how to instantiate the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture\"><code>ImageCapture</code></a> object.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> takePhotoButton <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">querySelector</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'button#takePhoto'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> canvas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">querySelector</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'canvas'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\ntakePhotoButton<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>onclick <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> takePhoto<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">takePhoto</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  imageCapture<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">takePhoto</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">blob</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Took photo:'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> blob<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    img<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>classList<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">remove</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'hidden'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    img<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>src <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token constant\">URL</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">createObjectURL</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>blob<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">catch</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">error</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">error</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'takePhoto() error: '</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> error<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/mediacapture-image/#dom-imagecapture-takephoto","title":"MediaStream Image Capture"}],"query":"api.ImageCapture.takePhoto"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.ImageCapture.takePhoto","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/takePhoto/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The takePhoto() method of the\n  ImageCapture interface takes a single exposure using the video capture\n  device sourcing a MediaStreamTrack and returns a Promise\n  that resolves with a Blob containing the data.","popularity":0.0004,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:54:54.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"ImageCapture.takePhoto()","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/imagecapture/takephoto","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/imagecapture/takephoto/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/b7556b71e1fc3e89057671b372871e9f33d3f0b8","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture","title":"ImageCapture"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageCapture/takePhoto","title":"ImageCapture.takePhoto()"}],"pageTitle":"ImageCapture.takePhoto() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}